            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p>
                Meybohm takes your privacy seriously and is strongly committed to preserving your privacy. Please read the following to learn more about our privacy policy.
            </p>

            <h2>What This Privacy Policy Covers</h2>
            <p>
                This policy covers how Meybohm Realtors, LLC, a Georgia Limited Liability Corporation (herein referred to as Meybohm or Meybohm Realtors) treats personal information that Meybohm collects and receives, including information related to your past use of Meybohm products and services. Personal information is information about you that is personally identifiable like your name, address, email address, or phone number, and that is not otherwise publicly available.
            </p>

            <h2>Information Collection and Use</h2>
            <p>
                Meybohm collects personal information when you register with Meybohm, when you use Meybohm products or services and when you visit Meybohm web pages. When you register we ask for information such as your name and email address and attributes about property listings that may interest you. Once you register with Meybohm, you are not anonymous to us. Meybohm automatically receives and records information on our server logs from your browser, including your IP (Internet Protocol) address, Meybohm cookie information (see below), and the page or pages you request. Meybohm uses information for the following general purposes: to customize the advertising and content you see, fulfill your requests for products and services, improve our services, contact you, conduct research, and provide anonymous reporting for internal and external clients.
            </p>
            <p>
                Under no circumstances does Meybohm Realtors sell, share or disclose personally identifiable information about its customers or website visitors to other individuals, companies or third-parties.
            </p>

            <h2>Cookies</h2>
            <p>
                Our Sites use a technology called "cookies". A cookie is a tiny element of data that our Sites can send to your browser, which may then be stored on your hard drive so we can recognize you when you return. All pages on our Sites where you are prompted to log in or that are customizable require that you accept cookies. If you have registered with our Sites, these cookies (1) may let us know who you are, (2) are necessary to access your account information (stored on our computers) in order to deliver personalized services to you, and (3) will provide us and our service providers with information that we will use to personalize our Sites in accordance with your preferences. Cookies are also required to optimize your website experience in that they keep up with your selected property search criteria and email address. You may set your Web browser to notify you when you receive a cookie. However, should you decide not to accept cookies from our Sites, you will limit the functionality we can provide when you visit our Sites.
            </p>

            <h2>Your Ability to Edit and Delete Your Information and Preferences</h2>
            <p>
                You can edit the information that is maintained about you via the website by visiting the Property Search or Search Criteria page. Users will only receive electronic mail correspondence from Meybohm Realtors when this information has been directly or indirectly requested. Meybohm does not send anonymous, spam or unsolicited email messages to its users, customers or site visitors. Even so, users can opt out of receiving future communications by clicking on the "Unsubscribe" link in any email correspondence received from Meybohm Realtors or simply by replying to any email received from Meybohm Realtors with a brief explanation regarding their wishes not to be contacted.
            </p>

            <h2>Confidentiality and Security</h2>
            <p>
                We limit access to personal information about you to Meybohm Realtors employees who we believe reasonably need to come into contact with that information to provide products or services to you or in order to do their jobs. We have physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards in place to protect personal information about you. To learn more about security, please contact Meybohm Realtors.
            </p>
            <p>
                Meybohm Realtors will never encourage children to use our websites, and will never market products or services to children.
            </p>

            <h2>Additional Information about Our Sites</h2>
            <p>
                In general, you can visit our Sites without telling us who you are or providing us with any information. However, we collect the IP (Internet protocol) addresses of all visitors to our Sites and other related information such as page requests, browser type, operating system and average time spent on our Sites. We use this information to monitor and improve our Sites.
            </p>

            <h2>Third Party Links</h2>
            <p>
                Our Sites may include links to the websites of our business partners, vendors and advertisers. Except as provided herein, we will not provide any of your personal information to these third parties without your prior consent.
            </p>
            <p>
                Meybohm Realtors provides links to third party websites as a convenience to the user. The inclusion of any link does not imply Meybohm Realtors' endorsement of any other company, its websites, or its products and/or services. These linked websites have separate and independent privacy policies, which we recommend you read carefully. We have no control over such websites and therefore have no responsibility or liability for the manner in which the organizations that operate such linked websites may collect, use or disclose and otherwise treat your personal information.
            </p>

            <h2>Security of Personal Information</h2>
            <p>
                We will maintain the confidentiality of all personal information collected via our Sites. We maintain administrative, technical and physical safeguards to protect against unauthorized access, use, modification and disclosure of personal information in our custody and control.
